main event: An observation of a bright light with clear shape moving at 600-1000 M.P.H. in Napa, California on 15th April 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed from the ground, by ground radar, and from the air, with no intercept attempted.
It was a naked eye observation lasting 30 seconds, and the object changed direction at some point.
Weather conditions were clear with a wind speed of 9 knots at 10232 ft altitude.
The evaluation labeled the source as 'unknown' with 'insufficient data for evaluation'.
A credible witness, Diane Robinson, reported the object moving at 10222 ft altitude, with no sound heard from the object.
